  "bib_entries": {
    "14442939": {
      "title": "Minimal vanishing sums of roots of unity with large coefficients",
      "abstract": "A vanishing sum , where ζ n is a primitive nth root of unity and the a i s are non-negative integers is called minimal if the coefficient vector (a 0 , … , a n−1 ) does not properly dominate the coefficient vector of any other such non-zero sum. We show that for every c∈ℕ there is a minimal vanishing sum of nth roots of unity with its greatest coefficient equal to c, where n is of the form 3pq for odd primes p, q. This solves an open problem posed by Lenstra Jr."
    }
